items.sentence: I didn't know that you were going to be here.
I didn't know that you were from Boston, too.
I didn't know that you wanted to work for me.
I didn't know that Tom would change his mind.
I didn't know that Tom was a friend of yours.
I didn't know that Tom use to live in Boston.
I didn't know that Tom could do that so well.
I didn't know Tom would care if you did that.
I didn't know Tom would allow you to do that.
I didn't even know that you liked basketball.
